The Makhado Municipality has issued a notice informing residents that there will be an interruption of power supply on the Levubu East line on Tuesday, 4 September, from 09:00 to 14:30 starting at pole number BE120 up to BE261. “The interruption is necessary to enable the municipality to re-install the Landman auto recloser only. No guarantee can be given that the electricity supply will be interrupted during the entire specified time. You are therefore warned that Council’s electrical lines must be considered live during the entire period,” stated the municipality. They said that the interruption will be subject to fair weather conditions.